.SH NAME
.PP
\f[V]hr\f[R] - horizontal rule for the terminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[V]hr\f[R] [\f[I]OPTIONS\f[R]] [NOTE \&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[V]hr\f[R] is a utility for displaying a horizontal rule in a
terminal.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
-h, --help
show help and exit
.TP
--version
show version and exit
.TP
-w, --width \f[I]CHARS\f[R]
target rule width (default: terminal width)
.TP
-d, --default \f[I]CHARS\f[R]
default target rule width (default: 80)
.TP
-a, --ascii
use ASCII lines (default: use Unicode lines)
.TP
-t, --time
show time
.TP
-f, --format \f[I]FORMAT\f[R]
time format (default: \f[V]%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\f[R])
.RS
.PP
The following format codes are supported:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]%Y\f[R] - four-digit year
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]%y\f[R] - two-digit year
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]%m\f[R] - two-digit month
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]%d\f[R] - two-digit day
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]%H\f[R] - two-digit hour using 24-hour clock
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]%I\f[R] - two-digit hour using 12-hour clock
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]%p\f[R] - locale equivalent of AM or PM
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]%M\f[R] - two-digit minute
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]%S\f[R] - two-digit second
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]%q\f[R] - twelve-digit picosecond
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]%z\f[R] - UTC offset
.RE
